    "80419 43) and the pretrained models used for dental SR predictions are available on Mendeley Data (https:// doi. org/ 10.",
    "17632/ 4xvx4 p9tzv.1).The out-of-fold validation results (Table 2) suggest that the 2D baseline model performs best and that the 3D baseline model yields the lowest performance.",
    "The analysis is based on traditional pixel-wise comparisons to highresolution images.",
    "However, the analysis of osteochondral ex vivo samples shows that the 2D structure model is the best for predicting microstructural bone details (r BVTV = 0.817 ± 0.005).",
    "Furthermore, averaging the prediction on three orthogonal planes did not improve the result."
